ref-5-3-2                    Xerox Quintus Prolog Reference Manual                      Section 5-3-2: File SpecificationsA file specification is one ofFile        where File is an atom which is either an absolute or relative file            name as defined by the operating system.library(File)            where File is an atom which is a relative file name.  File (or            File.pl) is sought in the directory path defined by the user            predicate library_directory/1.user        where 'user' is the absolute file name of the "pseudo-file" that is            connected to the user's terminal.  This pseudo-file is always open            for both input and output and cannot be closed.  Its input stream            is 'user_input' and its output stream is 'user_output'.